I just got back from UDA camp.  We did a lot better than expected.  We got a lot of Blue ribbons (1-3 mistakes in the dances you learned) and more Reds (3-5 mistakes) than we'd like.  The girls that got reds where SO upset. . . This was my LAST camp THANK GOD!  I'm not a good learn a dance in a hour perfrom it the next day kinda person.  I did however have to try out for "All-Stars" this year.  For All Stars you learn 2 8counts of jazz, 2 8counts of hip hop, and 2 8counts of pom, then make up 2 of your own 8counts.  Well I did it.  I went out there kinda messed up but didnt freeze was sharp smiled. . . . I was VERY happy with my performance.  But I did not get All-Stars. . . not that I expected that I would get it but it would have been nice. . . To be able to say LOOK I CAN DO SOMETHIGN GOOD!!!  6 girls tried out for all stars from bossier. . . 12 from the camp. . . they took I think 6 or 7 girls. . . Everyone from Bossier got it except me. . . Needless to say I was heart broken. . . It was SO hard not to cry.  At the end Chels started crying cuz it was her last year and I went ahead and cried and let everyone think I was crying because I was sad it was our last camp.  Yeah right! lol I hate camp.  But since I'm an officer I was invited to go to the Macy's Thanksgiving Parade in New York.  I can't wait to do that!  It cost around $2000.  PLUS spending money!  Fun times huh.  But we got 2nd place for our hometown rouine!  Very VERY good!  hehe Plus we got drill down CHAMPS and A Superer Throphy and uhmmm spirt stick and the "on the ball award"  which is basically a beach ball! lol  Well I'm very tired.  More camp detail  lata.

Recap since I've been gone.  
Thursday- I worked.  Uhhh I think I ran pizzas bussed tables and did kid check and I had to close the whole showroom which is HUGE.
Friday-  Went to dance clinic and then i went home fought with my gpa and as sad as this may sound went on my first "car date".  Carl came pick me up we went saw 50 First Dates (it was so awesome!  I wanted to cry and laugh at the same time! Must see!) then he drove me home.  We had so much fun.  And normally I get kinda nervous being in cars with teens but I felt totally safe.  
Sat-  Got my hair cut then just chilled until I had to go to work.  That was the longest work day EVER for me.  I bused tables then kid check.  Then cleaned the balcony.  Its hard to get smushed crackers out of carpet under booths.
Sun-  Church then work.  I did merchindise.  Then I closed for this other chick.  All I had to do was clean the bevrage bar and vaccum kid check and sweep a lil.  No biggie.  But it was our manger Mikes bday.  So we told him sumthing was wrong with the show then got him out there and told him happy birthday and had a cake out for him.  There was 36 candles on it so it started melting the lil sign so he blew out the candles.  Then this guy names Kyle took all the candles off really fast and he smashed it in mikes face.  Mike took the cake off his face and kyle took off running and mike just threw it and it hit the bevreage bar.  Then later on mike got sum cake pushed it in kyles face, put him in a trash can and rolled him outside.  It was too funny.  I didnt see the second half cuz I was workin but kyle told me and I saw polaroids on the board.  lol  Then kyle got cake all over my pants.  the nerd.
today is monday!
today was boring and I got dance clinic later.
